     1|/**
     2| * BLOCK 1 — Owner Session Preflight (runs before ANY owner-gated IVX IA action).
     3| *
     4| * A single, reusable gate that proves a REAL owner Supabase session exists before
     5| * the app POSTs to an owner-gated route (Owner AI chat, Gmail OAuth setup, Capital
     6| * Outreach actions, Power Tools actions, CRM/Gmail draft actions). Instead of a
     7| * generic "Owner session token unavailable" or a misleading /public/chat fallback,
     8| * a failed preflight surfaces an explicit `OWNER_SESSION_REQUIRED` result so the
     9| * owner is told to re-authenticate and the original action payload is preserved.
    10| *
    11| * The ten required checks (owner spec):
    12| *   1. Supabase session exists (before any POST).
    13| *   2. A real access_token exists.
    14| *   3. The synthetic dev-open-access-token is BLOCKED in production (strict mode).
    15| *   4. The owner email is detected.
    16| *   5. The owner email is allowlisted.
    17| *   6. The token issuer matches the app's Supabase project.
    18| *   7. Missing/expired session → do NOT POST.
    19| *   8. Returns OWNER_SESSION_REQUIRED (not a generic failure).
    20| *   9. Preserves the original action/prompt payload (caller keeps its own input).
    21| *  10. Never falls back to /public/chat (the caller must honor `ok:false`).
    22| *
    23| * Never logs or returns the raw access token.
    24| */
